      },
      "date": "2011-12-16 07:19:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nThe patch looks reasonable.\n\nIn order to get this included into master I think two things are needed:\n- update the dev_set_rdonly patches to indicate this patch is no longer needed, and is only included for testing and ease of using the same kernel with older Lustre versions.  The testing functionality can be replaced in Linux 3.0 by the dm-flakey driver, but little point in replacing one patch with another to get this into older kernels.\n- I don't see that filter_iocontrol() is modified to check for the error return from lvfs_set_rdonly() (this function is not in the orion branch, since OFD uses the OSD API)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
